g.text: UML Diagram: Class Code in Context
- Move the mouse cursor over a name to see more information.
- Click on a name to go to the corresponding page.

a.title: ― CodePosition: An index within an order intended for presentation (even though the content within levels of the hierarchy may be conceptually unordered). Expressed as an integer counting upward from 01 or 1.
a.xlink:title: ― CodePosition: An index within an order intended for presentation (even though the content within levels of the hierarchy may be conceptually unordered). Expressed as an integer counting upward from 01 or 1.

a.title: ― CodeRelationship: Source target relationship between codes in a code relation structure.
a.xlink:title: ― CodeRelationship: Source target relationship between codes in a code relation structure.

a.title: ― CodeList: List of codes and associated categories.
a.xlink:title: ― CodeList: List of codes and associated categories.

a.title: ― Category: Concept whose role is to define and measure a characteristic.
a.xlink:title: ― Category: Concept whose role is to define and measure a characteristic.

a.title: ― Notation: Representation of a category in the context of a code or a classification item, as opposed of the corresponding instance value which would appear when used in a dataset.
a.xlink:title: ― Notation: Representation of a category in the context of a code or a classification item, as opposed of the corresponding instance value which would appear when used in a dataset.

a.title: ― IndividualMember: Distinct element that is not itself a collection (atomic).
a.xlink:title: ― IndividualMember: Distinct element that is not itself a collection (atomic).

a.title: ― Sign: Something that suggests the presence or existence of a fact, condition, or quality.
a.xlink:title: ― Sign: Something that suggests the presence or existence of a fact, condition, or quality.

a.title: ― Identifier: Identifier for objects requiring short- or long-lasting referencing and management.
a.xlink:title: ― Identifier: Identifier for objects requiring short- or long-lasting referencing and management.

a.title: ― denotes: A definition for the code. Specialization of denotes for categories.
a.xlink:title: ― denotes: A definition for the code. Specialization of denotes for categories.

a.title: ― hasTarget: Note that this can be realized as a collection to support tuples.
a.xlink:title: ― hasTarget: Note that this can be realized as a collection to support tuples.
